==English==
===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /piːl/
*[[SAMPA]]: /pi:l/
**Homophones: [[peel]]
**Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːl|-iːl]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A loud sound, or a succession of loud sounds, as of bells, thunder, cannon, shouts, laughter, of a multitude, etc.
#* '''1883:''' [[w:Robert Louis Stevenson|Robert Louis Stevenson]], ''[[w:Treasure Island|Treasure Island]]''
#*: And, falling on a bench, he laughed until the tears ran down his cheeks, I could not help joining; and we laughed together, '''peal''' after '''peal'''...

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

#To sound with a peal or peals.
#*'''1864:''' [[w:Henry Wadsworth Longfellow|Henry Wadsworth Longfellow]], ''Christmas Bells''
#*: Then pealed the bells more loud and deep...
#*'''2006:''' [http://www.nytimes.com/2006/09/11/nyregion/nyregionspecial3/11bush.html?pagewanted=2&ei=5094&en=e468f88da52557ed&hp&ex=1158033600&partner=homepage New York Times]
#*: ''The bell pealed 20 times, clanging into the dusk as Mr. Bush’s motorcade drove off.''
----

